[div class=p 
	"Well, this is a nearly 4 hour long Resident Evil 4 glitchfest. Given the amount of glitches that were made in this TAS, I think I can call it a glitchfest, but playaround is also fine.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This TAS was made in new game plus (because obviously, starting with all weapons greatly increases the possibility of glitches), from a new round save and here we get into a small problem (or a big one, maybe). I wasn't aware that for TASes that start on a SRAM save, a verification movie was required (my mistake here, there's no excuse and I didn't look at the rules for that). Because of that, I ended up doing the entire TAS on top of a save I downloaded from the internet lol. I just wanted a save with everything unlocked to start TAS. So, as you noticed, I don't have a verification movie of the save that was used.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Okay, but why am I submitting this TAS here, even though I don't have a save verification movie? For two reasons:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		"This TAS is a glitchfest. So, in my opinion, a verification movie wouldn't be that necessary, since I'm not competing for time with anyone. The save that was used doesn't matter that much, since TAS is 100% based on messing around and doing as many glitches as possible.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"A save verification movie for a game like Resident Evil 4 would be extremely tedious and insanely long, since unlocking everything involves beating the game several times (to unlock the extras and then to leave a "new round" save with the weapons I wanted), beating Separate Ways (to unlock Chicago) and still getting 5 stars in all the Mercenaries scenarios, with all the characters (to unlock Handcannon). We're talking about a movie of more than 15 hours, maybe.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"So, these are the reasons that made me submit this TAS here, even though I don't have a verification movie. But of course, if these reasons are not valid, so be it. I just won't miss the opportunity to submit a TAS that, in my opinion, would be nice to have on the site.
	$LF
]div
