[h3 id=Glitches 
	[b 
		"Glitches
		$LF
	]b
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Many glitches have occurred in this TAS, but few have any documentation. I will comment here on some that were frequent.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		"When Leon jumps, whether it's from a fence or from a high place, he lands on the ground. However, at some points in the game, if you're in a specific position and jump, Leon ends up landing inside an object or even inside the ground. This causes him to lose collision with the ground and walls and allows you to exit the map. This glitch occurs in several parts of the game, in several different ways, but the way it works is the same. See examples 
		[a href=https://youtu.be/ipIRwfii3RI?t=357 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"here
		]a
		" and 
		[a href=https://youtu.be/ipIRwfii3RI?t=1873 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"here
		]a
		".
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Still on the glitch above, if Leon jumps much further than he should, he ends up losing all collision with the ground and falling forever. See at minute 
		[a href=https://youtu.be/ipIRwfii3RI?t=1840 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"30:40
		]a
		" and 
		[a href=https://youtu.be/ipIRwfii3RI?t=11964 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"3:19:24
		]a
		".
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"For some reason, the game developers sped up Leon's animation aiming the Striker. As a result, if you aim the Striker and before the crosshair appears, you enter the briefcase and equip another weapon, Leon will accelerate, almost twice as fast. This is a very famous glitch called "Ditman Glitch", used a lot in speedruns and also a lot in this TAS because it causes other glitches.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"Apparently, if you dodge a ganado's attack while the Ditman glitch is activated, you can stab objects or ganados from a distance. You'll see this on the farm, when I destroyed a crate from a distance (more specifically at minute 
		[a href=https://youtu.be/ipIRwfii3RI?t=483 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"8:03
		]a
		" of my encode) and also in the castle, in the part with the cultists with RPG, when I stabbed the cultists from a distance (minute 
		[a href=https://youtu.be/ipIRwfii3RI?t=4384 rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"1:13:04
		]a
		"). I'm not sure how this glitch works, much less why it occurs.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"When Leon is grabbed, takes damage from a ganado, does a jump animation or a kick animation, at the same time as a grenade or an RPG explodes, he does not take damage from the explosion.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		"When there is a narrow corner with a door and that door is opened, with Leon in the corner, he ends up inside the door and the enemies get confused. You will see this in the part before Bitorez's house, minute 
